        "committer": {
          "name": "Li Wei",
          "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-10-15 06:20:34.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5533 ptlrpc: Update imp_msghdr_flags at CONNECTING state",
        "message": "LU-5533 ptlrpc: Update imp_msghdr_flags at CONNECTING state\n\nErrors like\n\n  LustreError: 13507:0:(layout.c:2042:__req_capsule_get()) @@@ Wrong\n  buffer for field `dlm_rep' (1 of 1) in format `LDLM_INTENT_GETATTR':\n  0 vs. 112 (server)\n    req@ffff880ecfc8c000 x1476486707242176/t0(0)\n    o101->soaked-MDT0000-mdc-ffff881029559c00@192.168.1.108@o2ib:12/10\n    lens 576/192 e 0 to 0 dl 1408692442 ref 1 fl Complete:R/2/0 rc 0/0\n\nturned out to be early replies being mistook as normal ones.  What\nhappened was:\n\n  1. Client sent an ENQUEUE request with MSGHDR_AT_SUPPORT.\n\n  2. Client reconnected (CONNECTING -> RECOV) because of some other\n     request when Server was processing the ENQUEUE request.\n\n  3. Client resent the request without MSGHDR_AT_SUPPORT because the\n     resend happened before the imp_msghdr_flags update.  (The race is\n     clearly a problem.)\n\n  4. Client received an early reply for the initial \"generation\" of\n     the request, mistook it to be a normal reply because of the\n     absence of MSGHDR_AT_SUPPORT in the request buffer, and attempted\n     to find an ldlm_reply buffer in the reply.  (Here, using request\n     buffers to interpret replies is not really robust, since we reuse\n     the same request buffer for resends and there is no guarantee\n     against arrivals of replies for previous sending attempts.  This\n     applies to both MSGHDR_AT_SUPPORT and MSGHDR_CKSUM_INCOMPAT18.)\n\nThe problem in step 4 is not easy to fix without interoperability\nconsequences; this patch only fixes the race in step 3.  Because all\nrelevant versions at this point support AT and will have\nMSGHDR_CKSUM_INCOMPAT18 set, the problem described in step 4 will not\nshow up.\n\nChange-Id: If3f2d0dcbd2fad14e1ab581025ef42f5c7cc43c7\nSigned-off-by: Li Wei <wei.g.li@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
